conjecture: For a restricted partition lambda with distinct parts, there exists a nontrivial Markov chain on S_n(lambda) whose stationary distribution is F*_mu(x_1,...,x_n; q=1, t) / P*_lambda(x_1,...,x_n; q=1, t) for mu in S_n(lambda), where the transition probabilities are not described using the polynomials F*_mu.
author: Lauren Williams
